  <brief_title>Is Diverting Ileostomy Necessary in Stapled Ileoanal Pouch?</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Mansoura University</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Mansoura University</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Total proctocolectomy with ileal pouch anal anastomosis is the first choice surgical
      operation for management of ulcerative colitis and familial adenomatous polyposis. The
      addition of diverting ileostomy may reduce septic complications. In this randomized study the
      investigators compare two groups of patients with stapled ileoanal pouch one of them had
      diverting ileostomy and in the other this step is omitted.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
